title: Led Zeppelin - 1970.03.07 Montreux, Switzerland
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1970.03.07 Montreux, Switzerland   

Led Zeppelin
1970.03.07
Montreux, Switzerland
Montreux Casino

Audience Recording, except where noted.
"Divinity" - Atlantic Ocean Records

Details: 
This recording has all of the virtues of both soundboard and audience. 
There is very little audience noise and all of the instruments are 
perfectly balanced except for the lower notes, which are dominating 
throughout.

Tracklist:
Disc 1
101 - We're Gonna Groove
102 - I Can't Quit You Baby
103 - Dazed and Confused
104 - Heartbreaker
105 - White Summer

Disc 2
201 - Since I've Been Loving You
202 - Organ Solo
203 - Thank You
204 - What is and What Should Never Be
205 - Moby Dick
206 - How Many More Times
207 - Whole Lotta Love

"How Many More Times" and "Whole Lotta Love" are from 
the (inferior) soundboard source.
Whole Lotta Love is complete on this release.

Comments: Talk about energy. The audience is rowdy and loud and the 
group feed off of this to offer a killer show, with some of the best 
playing ever, and surely the best live version of Heartbreaker ever 
played. The audience recording captures the energetic atmosphere 
perfectly
